3:01 PM (64-06) Defendant Samuel W Webb appeared  in court, in custody.  Attorney B'Ivory LaMarr in court for Samuel W Webb.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin ADA TenHaken  in court. 
State called to the stand as a witness, Detective Kevin Warnecke.
Kevin Warnecke duly sworn by the clerk and testified on direct examination by ADA TenHaken.
Witness identified the defendant in Court. Exhibit #1 marked, identified and discussed in Court.
Exhibit #1 offered and received by the Court.
3:20PM - Cross examination by Attorney LaMarr.
3:27PM - Re-direct by the State.
3:28PM - Re-cross by Defense.
3:28PM - Argument by the State. Requesting bind over.
3:29PM - Argument by the Defense. Requesting dismissal.
Court finds probable cause that a felony has been committed and that the defendant likely committed it and binds him over to stand trial on the charges. 
Attorney B'Ivory acknowledge receipt of the Information, waived reading and plead not guilty to all charges on behalf of his client.
Speedy Trial requested.
Jury trial - 12 person on November 28, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendants Motion to Dismiss Complaint and Motion to Dismiss for Lack of Personal Jurisdiction are denied.

Defendant Samuel W Webb appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney B'Ivory LaMarr in court for Samuel W Webb.  Attorney Andrew Herrmann in court for State of Wisconsin. Called @ 9:38 a.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court on Defense motion to dismiss. 
9:39 a.m. - Court addresses Atty. Webb as to any further argument.  He does.
9:39 a.m. - Argument by Atty. Webb
9:45 a.m. - Response by the Court who finds "contract" argument a red herring and State does not need to address.
9:45 a.m. - Argument by the State in support of their position and asks the Court to den
9:46 a.m. - Response by the Court who refers to State vs. Haugen and based upon that case and arguments before the Court finds that reasonable inferences can be drawn based on other acts and denies the motion and addresses scheduling of preliminary hearing. Court also denies any pending motion to dismiss as to jurisdiction. 
Court goes off the record for scheduling.
9:49 a.m. - Court goes back on the record. State to file order.
Parties have nothing further. Court in recess.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
Defendant's Reply In Support of Motion to Dismiss Complaint

Defendant Samuel W Webb appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney B'Ivory LaMarr in court for Samuel W Webb.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court by JJ Crawford. Called @ 9:30 a.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court on motion to modify bond and to schedule the motions to dismiss filed by DE. Court schedules the motions to dismiss first and turns to the State as to motion to modify bond. 
Argument by the State who is objecting to motion to modify bond.
Response/argument by Atty. LaMarr who responds to further questions of the Court regarding change in circumstances.
Response by the Court who denies the motion at this time. 
Atty. LaMarr asks about preliminary hearing. Response by the Court who indicates the motions to dismiss must be heard prior to any preliminary hearing.
Parties have nothing further. 
Court in recess.
Motion hearing scheduled for September 22, 2022 at 09:30 am.

NOTICE OF ARREST
Signed bond filed with the court.

Defendant will not possess any firearms, ammunition or other weapons. Defendant is to be booked and printed within twenty-four (24) hours. Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any victim(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  VICTIM(S)/RESIDENCE(S): NO CONTACT WITH A.A.F. Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any co-actor(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  CO-ACTOR(S)/RESIDENCE(S): NO CONTACT WITH TREVION GAULT. Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.
